The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are central topics in computer science. The use of stable sets and independent transversals suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on cliques and partitions of graphs suggests that it may also belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) or Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of inequalities and proofs suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
